Nigeria’s vice president, Prof Yemi Osinbajo has assured Nigerians that himself and President Muhammadu Buhari remain committed to improving the lot of the Nigerian people. Osinbajo took to his twitter handle @Profosinbajo on Wednesday, amid growing speculations that he is being cut off from position of influence in Aso Rock, to announce that he was at Federal Executive Council meeting with Buhari. “Today, President Muhammadu Buhari presided over the Federal Executive Council,” Osinbajo said. “We remain committed to improving the lot of the Nigerian people.”